Bruce Schneier wrote:

 >> More interestingly is the difference between encrypting each block three
 >> times and chaining with the result, versus three different passes of DES
 >> in CBC mode.  Bihman has a paper showing that the first is stronger (to
 >> be published sooner or later in a Springer volume), and Kaliski also has
 >> some results on the topic (presumably to be published somewhere).
 
Even with three different IVs?  I'd wondered about that, but I assumed that
individual chaining of each layer with a different IV would be stronger.
I'd like to see that paper.  I wonder if it's FTPable from anywhere?

